<methods>
<methodStep>
<description>
<section>
<para>
<literalLayout>Automatically logged volumetric soil water content data from several soil depths.</literalLayout>
</para>
</section>
</description>
<instrumentation>5TM and EC-5 volumetric water content sensors and automatic dataloggers (Decagon Devices Inc., WA, USA)</instrumentation>
</methodStep>
<sampling>
<studyExtent>
<description>
<section>
<para>3 groups of sensors were set in the 1 ha permanent plot of the LTER site. Sensors were inserted to 4, 15, 30, 45 and 60 cm depths, respectively. The sampling rate ranged between 10 and 30 min. Means of respective sensors were averaged and monthly mean volumetric water contents were calculated in 2011 and 2012. </para>
</section>
</description>
</studyExtent>
<samplingDescription>continual</samplingDescription>
</sampling>
</methods>
